    "body": "### Problem\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fe3fffc2-0aea-425e-92f6-274149024992\nNeoVim replaces the original cursor state with its own from the last mode (usually NORMAL)\n\nThis behaviour has mentioned in [#4867](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/4867), however was not solved yet, though the issue was closed\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nIn the terminal settings, set the cursor shape to something other than block\n\n`nvim --clean`\n<kbd>:q</kbd>\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeoVim should return cursor shape back to initial, respectfully to terminal’s default\nOr we may not switch cursor shape by default\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nIDK, because by default Vim does not change cursor shapes across its modes\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.4\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nApple Terminal 470\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nHomebrew",
